==English==
===Etymology===
Late Latin, from Greek [[συγκοπη]], from [[συν−]] + [[κοπτειν]] ‘strike, cut off’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'sɪŋkəpi/}}
*{{audio|en-us-syncope.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A loss of [[conscious]]ness when someone faints, a [[swoon]].
#:*'''1973''': the rapidly-whitening face, the miserable fixed smile, meant a '''syncope''' within the next few bars. — Patrick O'Brian, ''HMS Surprise''
# A way of making a word shorter by leaving out sounds or letters in the middle of it, for example by changing [[cannot]] to [[can't]].

